
// The code snippet demonstrates how to execute a specific workflow action named "openai-query" using the [execute] slot. It specifies the filename of the action and provides several arguments, including the model type, maximum tokens, and various input parameters like instruction, context, and query. This setup facilitates interaction with OpenAI's model, enabling customized queries and responses based on the provided context and instructions.
execute:magic.workflows.actions.execute
   name:openai-query
   filename:/modules/openai/workflows/actions/openai-query.hl
   arguments
      model:gpt-4o
      max_tokens:int:1500
      instruction:x:@.system-message
      context:x:@execute/@execute/*/context
      query:x:@.hl
